args: Can you feel our burning love for you?
Let the beat get you even more fired up!
I'll make your hearts beat crimson-hot.\nNow come—sing with me!
Move it! Comin' through!\nI said move, man!
Imperial soldiers are seconds away! If we\ndon't hurry, the town'll be under attack!
So they ambush us amid a crowd and\nstir up chaos to lower our morale...\nCertainly a sound tactic.
What gives? Why'd you hype us\nall up and go quiet?
(Everyone's been looking forward to\nthis concert so much...)
(If we cancel it, it'll mean all the hard\nwork we put in this summer will amount\nto nothing.)
(But I know what I have to do.)
We need to get everyone to safety.\nAfterward, we can intercept the enemy.
I thought you'd say that.\n...Even if it is a bummer.
Of course. I may be a pop star,\nbut I'm the leader of this land first.
And right now, I have a more important\njob than entertaining the masses.
I have to protect their very lives!\nNow, let's go!
We managed to save the town, but...
They already took down our seaside stage,\ntoo. Not my favorite plot twist. I suppose\nit's curtains for the Summer Sizzlers.
Aw, maaan... Guess all that hard work was\nfor nothin'.
It may have ended before we wanted it to,\nbut I don't think it was in vain.
All that training put a ＂spring＂ in our step\nwe'll never lose. Even if it IS summer.
It was a rather vociferous affair, but all\nthings considered, it could've been worse.
I have to agree with the spring metaphor.\nIt really was a light and breezy time.
I'm a bit ashamed at how indulgent I was\nwith this venture...

Ha ha! C'mon, it's nothing to be ashamed
of. Acting different from your usual self is
what Mym meant by performance with a
＂twist,＂ isn't it?
Even if we weren't able to put on a\nshow, we still had a blast practicing.\nThat's what matters most.
You're finally back.\nI was getting antsy waiting for you!
Oh! Sorry to leave you hanging.
I told you I was your very first fan, didn't I?\nThat means never abandoning you.
And as your fan, I can't let today end like\nthis. Neither can the rest of these folks!
Your fans await, my love.\nIt's your job as a pop star to send them\nhome with some unforgettable memories!
That huge crowd waited for us all this\ntime?!
(As the leader of a country and boy band\nboth, I thought I had to guide everyone\nby my hand.)
(But it is they who have guided me.)
(With so many people out there cheering\nfor us... We can shine even brighter than\never before!)
The Summer Sizzlers are back...\nand we'll never part ways again!
